dct_description_sm: Depths shown by soundings and spot-shading (at low water); relief by contours and spot heights.
Tides chart, bridge heights, table of signs and abbreviations (for buoys, river-bed makeup, wrecks, various rocks, "can," "nun," "spar").
Shows streets, railways, city plans, vegetation and marshland, various locations (Hebrew Orphan Asylum, juvenile asylum, deaf and dumb institution, cemeteries, etc.) reservoirs and waterways.
